<item>
            <title>[LU-5097] Test failure on test suite conf-sanity, subtest test_76a</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-5097</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue was created by maloo for Bob Glossman &amp;lt;bob.glossman@intel.com&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run: &lt;a href=&quot;http://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/0c9e055a-e0f8-11e3-9a8d-52540035b04c&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/0c9e055a-e0f8-11e3-9a8d-52540035b04c&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Have been seeing this fairly frequently lately on test runs for a lot of different patch, so high confidence it&apos;s not due to patches being tested.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Some instances both before and after test 76 was renamed 76a.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The sub-test test_76a failed with the following error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;max_dirty_mb is not saved after remount&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Info required for matching: conf-sanity 76a&lt;/p&gt;</description>
