                            <comment id="88392" author="jfc" created="Tue, 8 Jul 2014 01:14:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch has been landed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="88197" author="hongchao.zhang" created="Fri, 4 Jul 2014 15:15:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;the patch in &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4933&quot; title=&quot;Automatically tune the max_dirty_mb&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-4933&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-4933&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; has been landed, and this issue could be also closed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="84867" author="hongchao.zhang" created="Mon, 26 May 2014 13:57:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;the patch is tracked in &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4933&quot; title=&quot;Automatically tune the max_dirty_mb&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-4933&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-4933&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/10446/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/10446/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="84628" author="adilger" created="Wed, 21 May 2014 18:21:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The patch &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/10034&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/10034&lt;/a&gt; adds auto-tuning to max_dirty_mb that causes conf-sanity.sh test_76a to fail.  It was failing as test_76 even before the patch landed, but this was masked by TEI-1508.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The patch &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/10402&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/10402&lt;/a&gt; will revert &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/10034&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/10034&lt;/a&gt;, and it can be fixed before re-landing.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
